accepted format, yes.

26:39.348 --> 26:41.805
Is this the beginning
of a conversation here?

26:44.228 --> 26:46.970
Yes. Doug can read.

26:47.148 --> 26:49.013
What was the last book you read?

26:51.444 --> 26:52.604
You were in college.

26:52.779 --> 26:55.395
Last thing I read was a letter
canceling my scholarship

26:55.573 --> 26:57.154
when I couldn't play anymore.

26:57.325 --> 26:59.611
- OK. High school.
- I was a hockey player.

26:59.786 --> 27:01.492
The only thing I had to read
was a scoreboard.

27:01.704 --> 27:05.037
- And they graduated you?
- They revered me. I was a god.

27:05.208 --> 27:07.915
What a tragic commentary
on our times.

27:08.086 --> 27:10.577
State championships, my last game,

27:10.755 --> 27:13.792
300 people carried me
around their shoulders on the ice.

27:13.966 --> 27:16.628
It took the state police
two hours to break it up.

27:16.803 --> 27:19.966
What were you planning on doing
when your gladiating days were over?

27:20.181 --> 27:24.140
You can bet your tights I never thought
I'd be working a freak show like this.

27:24.310 --> 27:27.177
I'm surprised you don't chuck it all
and start your own think tank.

27:30.399 --> 27:32.390
So where'd you matriculate from?

27:37.990 --> 27:39.855
You were in college?

27:41.327 --> 27:42.692
I had tutors.

27:45.665 --> 27:46.996
Excellent tutors.

27:51.712 --> 27:54.875
Would you please find someplace
else to put your clubs?

27:57.009 --> 27:58.920
Man, would I love
to see you play hockey.

28:01.180 --> 28:02.636
Any day-

28:10.606 --> 28:12.517
You can do better than that. Come on.

28:22.952 --> 28:25.443
- Come on.
- Oh!

28:40.261 --> 28:41.717
That's one.

28:45.933 --> 28:47.264
Come on, take it. Take it.

28:50.605 --> 28:52.095
Cut it out.

29:04.327 --> 29:05.442
That's two.

29:09.707 --> 29:11.208
Stop it, you...

29:13.920 --> 29:15.251
Three.

29:16.923 --> 29:18.163
Four.

29:24.972 --> 29:26.508
You make me ill.

29:57.046 --> 29:59.162
It's not like his nose was perfect.

30:00.132 --> 30:02.168
He's the one who wanted to play.

30:03.302 --> 30:06.385
He's like those morons who go around
insisting you hit them in the stomach

30:06.555 --> 30:08.261
as hard as you can.

30:10.351 --> 30:14.811
I don't know why I'm explaining this to
you. All I did was play his stupid game.

30:14.981 --> 30:17.518
Next you'll be telling me
how guilty I sound.

30:17.733 --> 30:21.317
- Is not guilt.
- Well, at least we agree on that.

30:21.487 --> 30:25.526
- Is fear.
- You've gotta be kidding me.

30:25.700 --> 30:27.361
What do I have to be afraid of?

30:27.576 --> 30:30.409
Because finally you have
found yourself a partner.

30:34.750 --> 30:37.662
Oh, my God. I thought you
said it was just his nose.

30:42.133 --> 30:45.000
- What? What's wrong?
- He's all yours.

30:55.896 --> 30:57.932
Toe pick.

31:02.278 --> 31:03.734
Oh!

31:03.904 --> 31:07.943
- What's her problem?
- I think she is nervous about rematch.

31:08.117 --> 31:09.698
Hm...

32:14.392 --> 32:15.427
Kate.

32:18.729 --> 32:20.390
Mm-hm?

32:47.341 --> 32:49.002
You want my hands where?

32:53.347 --> 32:54.553
You gotta be kidding.

32:57.726 --> 32:59.933
- How am I doing?
- Maybe in about five years

33:00.104 --> 33:01.844
you'll get it up to half-speed.

33:03.232 --> 33:04.472
Hey.

33:04.650 --> 33:07.016
Hey, come on!

33:07.236 --> 33:09.022
Douglas?
Douglas, come back.

33:09.238 --> 33:11.194
You have the mentality
of a rock, you know that?

34:30.319 --> 34:31.775
Yes.

34:42.206 --> 34:44.413
Yes. Yes. Yes. Ah!

34:44.625 --> 34:47.958
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

34:51.465 --> 34:53.456
She's got everything.

34:53.634 --> 34:55.625
A house, the rink.

34:55.803 --> 34:57.213
I don't get it.

34:59.598 --> 35:02.590
You know something?
I don't even think she likes to skate.

35:02.810 --> 35:06.598
You worked in factory.
You were happy there?

35:06.772 --> 35:10.230
Hey, I worked there because I had to.

35:10.401 --> 35:12.187
Uh-huh.

35:42.308 --> 35:43.297
Just a moment, please.

35:44.435 --> 35:46.972
- Kate. Oh, you're...
- What the hell are you doing?

35:47.187 --> 35:49.564
- Did I say come in? Get out!
- No.

35:49.732 --> 35:52.644
Get out. Get out this second.

35:52.818 --> 35:55.355
I handle this stuff all the time.
It's not that big a mystery.

36:02.745 --> 36:04.360
- What's that?
- Open it up.

36:04.580 --> 36:06.946
Go on. I wrapped it myself.

36:09.543 --> 36:11.909
I looked in all the stores. What do you
get for the girl who has everything?

36:15.966 --> 36:17.251
An old shirt.

36:19.720 --> 36:22.336
An old shirt?
Bobby Hull wore that sweater.

36:22.556 --> 36:25.673
That's Bobby Hull's game sweater.
That...

36:25.851 --> 36:30.220
I've had that 15 years. Bobby Hull.

36:30.230 --> 36:32.846
- Forget it. I'll take it...
- No, no. I like it.

36:33.025 --> 36:34.561
- I'll get something else.
- No, I like it.

36:34.735 --> 36:36.441
- You'll tear it!
- Then let go!

36:41.492 --> 36:42.732
Thank you.

36:44.453 --> 36:46.535
So anyway, merry Christmas.

36:46.705 --> 36:48.411
Well, wait a minute.

36:58.842 --> 37:00.218
Merry Christmas.

37:20.030 --> 37:22.066
Great Expectations.

37:22.241 --> 37:25.825
Well, it was either that or
Curious George Plays Hockey.

37:28.539 --> 37:29.904
I took a chance.

37:32.668 --> 37:35.000
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

38:28.182 --> 38:30.798
- Hale?
- Kate.

38:31.018 --> 38:34.681
I was looking at your stuff.
Great pictures in here.

38:34.855 --> 38:38.439
That's your mom, right?
Boy, she was a knockout.

38:38.609 --> 38:42.352
Yes, she was very pretty.
She was a show skater.

38:42.529 --> 38:45.441
There's one over here.
You look too young to walk yet.

38:45.616 --> 38:47.152
You got skates on.

38:47.910 --> 38:50.242
What is this expression on your face?
Is that a smile?

38:50.412 --> 38:52.653
I never knew you had so many teeth.

38:53.415 --> 38:55.531
We usually keep this door
closed during a party.

38:55.709 --> 38:57.324
Am I some guy off the street?

38:57.544 --> 39:01.583
You probably didn't recognize me
in my rig here. It's pretty sharp, huh?

39:01.757 --> 39:02.963
$69.95.

39:05.010 --> 39:06.341
Turn around.

39:11.433 --> 39:13.173
- What are you doing?
- Turn around.

39:16.063 --> 39:19.396
Thank you.

39:23.195 --> 39:25.026
- Done?
- Yes.

39:27.324 --> 39:29.406
That book you gave me,
it's pretty good.

39:29.618 --> 39:32.360
Really? Using it as a doorstop
or a coaster?

39:32.538 --> 39:34.153
Very funny. Here.

39:34.331 --> 39:36.788
- No, I don't drink.
- It's only champagne.

39:36.959 --> 39:40.122
- I've never had a drink in my life.
- You're kidding.

39:40.295 --> 39:43.628
- You afraid you're gonna get fat?
- I hardly expect you to understand.

39:43.799 --> 39:44.834
- Kate.
- Hale.

39:45.008 --> 39:46.544
There you are.

39:46.718 --> 39:50.552
- Doug Dorsey, Hale Forrest.
- Well... finally.

39:51.598 --> 39:52.587
The secret weapon.

39:54.142 --> 39:55.097
In the flesh.

39:58.480 --> 40:02.018
- I guess this calls for a toast.
- Let's drink to the little people.

40:04.820 --> 40:06.776
I understand you were
at Minnesota State.

40:06.989 --> 40:08.229
For a while.

40:08.407 --> 40:10.443
I used to play
a little hockey myself. For fun.

40:12.995 --> 40:16.613
Sure. And maybe you
can stop by the office.

40:16.832 --> 40:19.244
- Help me with currency arbitrage.
- If you will excuse me,

40:19.459 --> 40:22.166
naked male insecurity
really leaves me cold.

40:26.466 --> 40:28.457
Must be tough to stay away.

40:28.635 --> 40:30.887
I understand you're
giving Kate a rough time.

40:31.054 --> 40:32.430
You know Kate.

40:33.932 --> 40:37.424
Yes, I do. And I don't like
to see her upset.

40:39.563 --> 40:42.521
If I was you, I'd invest in blindfolds.

41:08.675 --> 41:12.133
Seven, six, five,

41:12.304 --> 41:16.092
four, three, two, one.

41:16.266 --> 41:17.881
Happy New Year!

41:18.060 --> 41:19.425
Happy New Year!

41:28.236 --> 41:29.737
Happy New Year!

41:32.866 --> 41:33.855
Happy New Year!

41:36.244 --> 41:37.859
Happy New Year, sweetheart.

41:38.830 --> 41:40.411
Happy New Year!

42:22.791 --> 42:25.282
- Who is it?
- It's me, Kate.

42:41.184 --> 42:44.017
I spoke to Anton. He said you
were leaving for the weekend.

42:44.187 --> 42:46.678
- What, that's a problem?
- No, I think it's great.

42:46.857 --> 42:48.768
You haven't been home
since you got here.

42:48.942 --> 42:51.604
They probably think we've got you
under lock and key.

42:52.821 --> 42:55.107
- Come on in.
- I haven't been up here in a while.

42:55.323 --> 42:57.609
Not since Brian.
Brian had mirrors up all over.

42:57.826 --> 42:59.441
Yeah, I took them down.

42:59.619 --> 43:02.907
It's kind of a mess.
I wasn't expecting any company.

43:04.833 --> 43:06.243
What's this?

43:07.127 --> 43:08.367
That's me smelling the ice.

43:08.545 --> 43:10.752
I told this guy once
I loved how ice smelled.

43:10.922 --> 43:13.880
It became this thing.
Somebody got a camera.

43:14.051 --> 43:16.042
- I never thought about it.
- I'm not surprised.

43:16.219 --> 43:17.720
What's that supposed to mean?

43:17.888 --> 43:18.923
Kate.

43:19.097 --> 43:22.134
I'll be right there.
What did you mean by that?

43:22.309 --> 43:26.473
I think you'd skate even better
if you'd let yourself enjoy it a little.

43:26.646 --> 43:30.355
Wait. What's this? I come up to say,
"Have a nice weekend,"

43:30.525 --> 43:32.311
and you're gonna give me pointers?

43:32.527 --> 43:33.983
- You brought it up.
- No, I didn't.

43:34.196 --> 43:35.481
- Yes, you did.
- No, I didn't.

43:35.697 --> 43:37.278
- Yes, you did.
- No...

43:42.954 --> 43:44.660
I came to give you this.

43:44.831 --> 43:47.664
- What's that?
- It's our greatest hits.

43:49.002 --> 43:51.835
It's a video for your family
of us skating.

43:53.173 --> 43:55.664
- Thanks.
- My dad booked some extra rooms

43:55.842 --> 43:58.299
in Chicago, and we'd love them
to stay with us.

43:58.470 --> 44:01.633
- My family?
- Yes. To the Nationals.

44:01.848 --> 44:04.965
- They're coming, aren't they?
- I don't know.

44:05.685 --> 44:08.643
Look at all you've done.
They must be really excited.

44:08.647 --> 44:10.262
Honey, it's a 7:30 show.

44:10.440 --> 44:12.351
- You better go.
- Why wouldn't they come?

44:12.567 --> 44:14.683
They'll come, they're coming.
Hale's waiting.

44:14.861 --> 44:16.192
How do you know
if you haven't told them?

44:16.404 --> 44:17.814
- I'm gonna tell them.
- When?

44:18.573 --> 44:20.529
- Now. This weekend.
- You sure?

44:20.700 --> 44:22.565
- Yeah, I'm sure.
- Really?

44:22.744 --> 44:25.656
Kate, believe me.
I'm dying to tell them.

44:55.277 --> 44:57.734
Dougie? Dougie!

44:59.281 --> 45:00.236
What?

45:01.658 --> 45:03.319
Doug. Hey, you're a captain now.

45:10.041 --> 45:11.076
Come on, come on.

45:11.251 --> 45:13.708
Hey, would you let him up
for air, dear. Come on.

45:15.088 --> 45:17.670
I'll be a son of a bitch.

45:23.054 --> 45:24.715
Man, it's good to see you.

45:24.890 --> 45:26.596
Yeah, it's good to see you, too.

45:26.766 --> 45:29.599
Hey! My brother Doug,
home from the Merchant Marine.

45:31.188 --> 45:32.428
Did you forget
how to use the phone?

45:32.647 --> 45:34.933
Come on. Move back, move back.

45:35.108 --> 45:36.769
He's been cruising all over the world

45:36.943 --> 45:39.104
and he can't even get to the bar.
Come on.

45:39.321 --> 45:43.234
Hey, Ensign Dorsey. No, no...
Lieutenant, Captain Dorsey, huh?

45:43.408 --> 45:47.492
- Cool it with the Merchant Marine.
- What? Sh, sh!

45:47.662 --> 45:50.324
- What?
- I didn't join the Merchant Marine.

45:51.291 --> 45:53.031
- Still got your sea legs?
- Sh!

45:53.210 --> 45:56.623
If you weren't with the
Merchant Marine, where were you?

45:56.796 --> 45:59.412
Let's go outside
and talk about this.

45:59.633 --> 46:03.091
- We're all family here.
- Tell us about it.

46:03.303 --> 46:04.884
Come on. Tell me now.

46:06.431 --> 46:07.762
Come on, chief.

46:07.974 --> 46:12.013
Well, actually,
it's kind of interesting.

46:13.647 --> 46:14.807
Tell him.

46:21.154 --> 46:22.655
I've been doing a little...

46:24.199 --> 46:26.531
Been doing a little figure skating.

46:26.701 --> 46:28.487
- Damn.
- What'd he say?

46:29.871 --> 46:31.156
You been doing what?

46:32.165 --> 46:33.245
Finger painting?

46:37.003 --> 46:39.460
These people, they think
we can go all the way.

46:39.631 --> 46:41.087
All the way to where?

46:43.009 --> 46:46.046
To the Nationals. Walter, the cham...

46:47.180 --> 46:48.761
You just don't understand.

46:49.599 --> 46:51.135
Was it me? Was it something I did?

46:51.351 --> 46:53.137
I'm telling you, I'm good.

46:53.353 --> 46:57.596
Come on, Doug, you're a hockey player.
How good can you be?

46:57.774 --> 47:00.481
Face it. If you're lucky,
a year from now

47:00.652 --> 47:04.065
you're gonna be in a Snoopy costume
in the frigging Ice Capades.

47:04.239 --> 47:07.026
You know me better than that. You think
I'd spend 15 hours a day, every day,

47:07.242 --> 47:09.608
to win some consolation prize?

47:09.786 --> 47:12.744
- I'm talking an Olympic gold medal.
- It's the girl.

47:12.914 --> 47:14.825
You're mixed up with this broad.
That's it, isn't it?

47:15.041 --> 47:18.158
- It's a great opportunity.
- It's figure skating.

47:18.336 --> 47:20.827
And I like it!

47:21.006 --> 47:24.590
It's a lot goddamn harder than
playing hockey, I can tell you that.

47:24.759 --> 47:27.216
And the stuff we're doing,
it's gonna be different.

47:27.387 --> 47:31.300
The costumes, the music.
Everything is gonna be different.

47:31.474 --> 47:33.214
You'll see.

47:38.064 --> 47:40.180
Are they gonna make you
shave your legs?

47:40.358 --> 47:42.019
Screw this. I don't even know why...

47:46.406 --> 47:47.395
Gotcha.

47:48.783 --> 47:49.943
Ah!

47:50.118 --> 47:53.155
Good. This is looking good. Now.

47:54.539 --> 47:57.872
- Oh, I like it.
- It's not too low, is it?

47:58.043 --> 48:01.035
Well, we don't want him to hide
his light under a basket, do we?

48:01.254 --> 48:05.293
Now, where to put this? Here. Here.

48:06.384 --> 48:09.217
I know.

48:13.266 --> 48:14.847
Let's put it here.

48:15.518 --> 48:18.225
- What do you think you're doing?
- Just getting started.

48:29.074 --> 48:30.109
This is Mozart.

48:31.368 --> 48:34.826
- It's not us.
- The deal was that we had to listen.

48:36.247 --> 48:38.238
Kate, this is tired.

48:38.458 --> 48:41.245
Ten thousand other skaters will be
cueing up the same boring crap.

48:41.461 --> 48:45.249
This doesn't get it done.
It's like the costumes.

48:45.423 --> 48:47.414
Let's be different.

48:47.592 --> 48:49.423
Let's kick a little ass.

48:50.095 --> 48:52.086
If you wanna see some asses kicked,

48:52.305 --> 48:54.921
why don't you throw on some jeans
and skate to this.

48:57.143 --> 48:59.555
If you wanna win, you play it straight.

48:59.729 --> 49:01.811
This is boring.

49:06.528 --> 49:09.861
Unacceptable!

49:13.034 --> 49:15.446
- Would you stop?
- Didn't work for you last time!

49:15.620 --> 49:16.985
What?

49:17.163 --> 49:19.154
You heard me!

49:19.332 --> 49:22.824
- You have some nerve!
- Just listen to my music one second!

49:23.002 --> 49:24.958
Stop turning it!

49:25.130 --> 49:27.121
Guys.

49:28.007 --> 49:29.622
Hey!

49:32.762 --> 49:34.627
It's after midnight.

49:34.848 --> 49:36.429
I have a 6:30 appointment.

49:36.599 --> 49:38.339
We were just wrapping up.

49:40.937 --> 49:43.553
Play him the Mozart.
You'll be asleep in no time.

49:49.737 --> 49:54.106
Katya, please try to understand.
Douglas is not boy. He is man.

49:54.284 --> 49:57.196
- Is young, vigorous man.
- I don't care what you call him.

49:57.412 --> 50:00.154
He has three months to qualily for the
Nationals. He needs every minute.

50:00.331 --> 50:03.198
Sure, sure. This I know.
And he is back on Monday.

50:03.376 --> 50:06.493
- And he will be working much better.
- Really?

50:09.174 --> 50:11.165
Katya, please, you know.

50:11.384 --> 50:14.547
Solitude is...
Too much is not good, eh?

50:14.721 --> 50:17.178
It's Christmas, we skate.
I have the flu, we skate.

50:17.390 --> 50:19.506
I have a boyfriend in London
that I never see.

50:19.726 --> 50:23.310
I skate every day so that you can play
Dr. Frankenstein with this guy.

50:23.480 --> 50:25.937
I show up every morning
for seven months

50:26.107 --> 50:29.770
so that you can give him two days
to go off whoring in New York City?

50:29.944 --> 50:32.230
Is not entirely correct.

50:33.823 --> 50:35.063
He went to Boston.

51:40.473 --> 51:41.428
If I get her any higher,

51:41.599 --> 51:44.432
they'll need a putty knife to scrape
her off the ceiling. Am I right?

51:45.728 --> 51:47.810
- Are we ready for Nationals or what?
- We will be.

51:47.981 --> 51:51.599
- Celebrating? We haven't won.
- To you, Doug.

51:51.776 --> 51:55.564
Who's ready to order? I think
I'll start with some vichyssoise.

51:55.738 --> 51:59.322
Five weeks to go. Everything's starting
to click. We're gonna kick some tail.

51:59.534 --> 52:01.741
- Am I right?
- "Tail"? Excuse me?

52:01.911 --> 52:03.447
- Some beluga.
- I'm eligible.

52:03.621 --> 52:04.997
Doug Dorsey, licensed to thrill.

52:05.206 --> 52:06.946
Slow down, champ.
We've got a long way to go.

52:07.166 --> 52:09.828
- Trying to rain on my parade?
- Don't let her beat you down.

52:10.003 --> 52:12.085
Hasn't happened by now,
he's in the clear.

52:12.255 --> 52:14.667
You're standing there doing nothing.
Get our menu.

52:14.841 --> 52:18.459
- Now is not the time.
- Any specials or what?

52:18.636 --> 52:20.137
Everyone's in such a great mood.

52:20.305 --> 52:23.297
- I'll throw another log on the fire.
- Hale, now is not the time.

52:23.516 --> 52:26.599
They'll find out sooner or later.
The fact is

52:26.769 --> 52:29.852
I've asked Kate to marry me,
and she's accepted.

52:31.733 --> 52:34.145
- Fantastic.
- Oh, Hale, congratulations.

52:34.319 --> 52:35.855
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

52:36.070 --> 52:40.109
- That's great.
- Katya, I want my kiss.

52:40.283 --> 52:42.365
- Show them the ring, Kate.
- That's just great.

52:42.535 --> 52:44.901
Now, there's a piece of ice.

52:45.079 --> 52:47.661
Hale, I think I'm paying
you altogether too much.

52:47.832 --> 52:49.743
- What are you doing?
- We ready to order?

52:49.917 --> 52:51.623
- Yeah.
- Sure.

53:52.855 --> 53:54.686
Still dropping that shoulder.

53:57.568 --> 53:58.944
I thought you'd retired.

54:00.905 --> 54:02.520
I changed my mind.

54:04.784 --> 54:08.572
You know what I think
is the saddest thing about sports?

54:09.997 --> 54:11.828
People who stay too long
at the party.

54:13.167 --> 54:16.375
- What are you doing here, Rick?
- I'd like to see you go out a champion.

54:16.546 --> 54:18.411
That's my plan.

54:19.799 --> 54:22.757
If you wanted to skate so badly,
why didn't you come to me?

54:22.969 --> 54:25.756
- I know we've made some mistakes.
- Mistakes?

54:25.972 --> 54:28.759
You spent the last ten years
tying me into knots.

54:28.933 --> 54:30.434
