1:18:38.423 --> 1:18:40.914
Again, again. Again. Again.

1:18:44.888 --> 1:18:45.923
Katya, head up.

1:18:47.265 --> 1:18:50.723
Higher. Higher. She has to fly.

1:18:57.025 --> 1:18:59.232
- Are they gonna get it?
- Eventually.

1:19:00.570 --> 1:19:01.980
Before they kill each other?

1:19:06.326 --> 1:19:10.410
Release. Release must be total.
Is no halfway. Halfway is bullshit.

1:19:10.580 --> 1:19:12.992
You go halfway, you get hurt.

1:19:23.259 --> 1:19:25.966
Higher. Much higher.

1:19:27.430 --> 1:19:30.137
We are needing an explosion.

1:19:33.228 --> 1:19:35.264
on! on!

1:20:07.345 --> 1:20:08.425
Kate?

1:20:09.973 --> 1:20:12.589
I was just looking at
the pictures of Mother.

1:20:19.148 --> 1:20:20.684
I can hear her now:

1:20:20.858 --> 1:20:22.018
"The Olympics."

1:20:25.321 --> 1:20:26.857
It's what she always dreamed of.

1:20:29.575 --> 1:20:32.658
Look at this thing.
Just sitting here empty.

1:20:35.957 --> 1:20:37.493
We're almost there, honey.

1:20:38.960 --> 1:20:41.997
- I can taste it.
- What if it stays empty?

1:20:42.171 --> 1:20:46.130
Mm. Not this time. Go to bed.
You need your rest.

1:20:46.301 --> 1:20:47.791
I'm not tired.

1:20:47.969 --> 1:20:51.132
- Kate.
- No. What are we doing?

1:20:54.642 --> 1:20:56.303
Why am I doing this?

1:20:58.521 --> 1:21:00.227
It's what you've always wanted.

1:21:01.441 --> 1:21:02.726
Always?

1:21:06.612 --> 1:21:08.227
- Kate...
- I know.

1:21:09.824 --> 1:21:13.908
I'm going. These little pep talks
can be so exhausting.

1:22:02.377 --> 1:22:04.459
Opening ceremonies,
you enjoyed yourself?

1:22:04.629 --> 1:22:06.836
- It was great.
- Cold and great.

1:22:07.006 --> 1:22:09.998
So, Doug, what's the difference
between this and hockey?

1:22:10.968 --> 1:22:13.095
The women.

1:22:13.262 --> 1:22:15.173
What's the feeling?
Everybody out for themselves

1:22:15.348 --> 1:22:17.760
or is there a team spirit building?

1:22:18.810 --> 1:22:21.426
- Oh, we're definitely a team.
- Definitely.

1:22:22.313 --> 1:22:24.019
There's a real sense of togetherness.

1:22:24.190 --> 1:22:26.681
- Spirit.
- Spirit.

1:22:26.859 --> 1:22:29.692
Family. It's sort of...

1:22:30.321 --> 1:22:32.107
It's almost...

1:22:32.281 --> 1:22:34.146
- It's almost...
- Orgasmic.

1:22:35.118 --> 1:22:36.403
What did she say?

1:22:37.662 --> 1:22:40.119
- The Russians.
- The Russians.

1:22:40.289 --> 1:22:41.244
Nikolai?

1:22:42.417 --> 1:22:43.953
- Nikolai?
- Can we get a photo?

1:22:44.168 --> 1:22:45.453
You guys gonna be here a while?

1:23:11.320 --> 1:23:12.776
You forgot a button.

1:23:12.947 --> 1:23:14.403
No, I like it open.

1:23:16.534 --> 1:23:18.195
Well, it looks terrible.

1:23:18.411 --> 1:23:19.947
It pulls at my neck.

1:23:22.915 --> 1:23:24.451
You should've
mentioned that in Chicago.

1:23:24.625 --> 1:23:27.002
Enough.

1:23:35.052 --> 1:23:36.258
Button it.

1:23:37.221 --> 1:23:41.339
- We're on.
- Good luck.

1:23:46.772 --> 1:23:50.560
Representing the United States
of A men'ca, Moseley and Dorsey.

1:23:50.735 --> 1:23:53.477
- Button the goddamn button.
- Get over it.

1:23:53.654 --> 1:23:56.111
You are an immature asshole
of the lowest order.

1:23:57.783 --> 1:24:00.399
If it was 40 below and that button
meant the difference

1:24:00.620 --> 1:24:04.533
between a long satisfying life
and a horrible death from hypothermia,

1:24:04.707 --> 1:24:07.198
I still wouldn't give you
the satisfaction.

1:24:08.044 --> 1:24:09.204
Skate.

1:24:34.779 --> 1:24:36.110
A technical/y superior program,

1:24:36.322 --> 1:24:38.563
but did you feel there
was something missing?

1:24:38.741 --> 1:24:41.858
Absolute/y. They delivered all
the short program required moves,

1:24:42.036 --> 1:24:43.446
but it seemed very cold.

1:24:43.663 --> 1:24:46.530
As if we were seeing two
strangers, rather than a fluid pair.

1:24:47.750 --> 1:24:49.706
It just didn't look like
they were having fun out there.

1:24:53.548 --> 1:24:55.038
Hey, Doug.

1:24:55.216 --> 1:24:57.923
- Was the altitude a problem tonight?
- No.

1:25:00.304 --> 1:25:04.547
Long program. We've been hearing all
week about your new surprise move.

1:25:04.725 --> 1:25:06.465
- What's it called?
- The Pamchenko.

1:25:06.644 --> 1:25:09.807
- The Pamchenko. Is it named after...?
- We're not doing it.

1:25:09.981 --> 1:25:12.097
- What?
- We've taken it out of the program.

1:25:12.275 --> 1:25:15.483
- It's not ready.
- Doug?

1:25:18.489 --> 1:25:19.854
A button?

1:25:20.032 --> 1:25:22.523
- What in hell are you thinking of?
- Me?

1:25:22.702 --> 1:25:24.488
Yes, you. What the hell
is in your head?

1:25:24.704 --> 1:25:27.491
- He's making like this is my fault.
- You didn't deliver.

1:25:27.665 --> 1:25:28.996
What, you want a pat on the back?

1:25:29.166 --> 1:25:30.667
When did I become
the designated asshole?

1:25:30.835 --> 1:25:32.291
What happened? Ask the ice queen.

1:25:32.461 --> 1:25:35.669
- That'll be enough of that.
- Let me know when you're done, Jack,

1:25:35.840 --> 1:25:39.799
you can tell me why I spent five weeks
on a move she was never gonna do.

1:25:39.969 --> 1:25:42.130
- You're out of line.
- I needed the gold medal!

1:25:42.305 --> 1:25:44.512
Forget it!
We can win without the move.

1:25:44.682 --> 1:25:47.924
- Impossible.
- Where were you when this was going on?

1:25:48.102 --> 1:25:49.967
Where was I?
I was babysitting!

1:25:50.146 --> 1:25:53.013
Loud and clear, folks:
Losing gracefully does nothing for me!

1:25:53.190 --> 1:25:56.353
- Think about that in the future!
- That what you told Brian in Calgary?

1:25:59.864 --> 1:26:02.571
You can kid all you want about
what happened. I've seen the tapes.

1:26:02.742 --> 1:26:06.326
Brian was getting it done.
Ask him. He'll tell you.

1:26:07.913 --> 1:26:09.494
All right, Douglas, is enough.

1:26:09.707 --> 1:26:12.790
Today, it's about a button.
You people are all excuses.

1:26:12.960 --> 1:26:14.996
- You wanna point a finger...
- You goddamn son of a bitch.

1:26:15.171 --> 1:26:16.957
Gotta find that go-to guy.

1:26:17.131 --> 1:26:19.338
You should've started
with a go-to girl, Jack.

1:26:19.508 --> 1:26:20.543
- That cuts it!
- He's right.

1:26:20.718 --> 1:26:22.174
What?

1:26:22.845 --> 1:26:24.130
He's right. He is.

1:26:27.892 --> 1:26:29.132
All of it.

1:26:30.728 --> 1:26:32.764
We worked so hard for two years.

1:26:33.898 --> 1:26:35.638
And I just went and threw it all away.

1:26:44.659 --> 1:26:46.945
- Why did you stay with me?
- Kate, don't.

1:26:48.913 --> 1:26:52.371
Don't what? Tell the truth?

1:26:55.211 --> 1:26:56.872
We can't buy back what happened today.

1:26:58.714 --> 1:27:00.215
We can't start over.

1:27:02.093 --> 1:27:04.630
Do you think I look at myself,
at what I've become,

1:27:04.804 --> 1:27:06.419
and do you think I'm proud?

1:27:07.932 --> 1:27:12.050
- What do you want?
- I don't know.

1:27:15.147 --> 1:27:16.978
Iguess I would like
to go back to the beginning

1:27:17.149 --> 1:27:21.313
and have you say, win or lose,
I could just be your daughter.

1:27:27.034 --> 1:27:28.899
You came every day, and you skated.

1:27:31.247 --> 1:27:33.659
This must've been
like a nightmare for you.

1:27:39.797 --> 1:27:42.755
I didn't know it was
gonna end up like this.

1:27:49.890 --> 1:27:51.221
I'm sorry.

1:27:56.897 --> 1:27:59.309
I'm so sorry. For everything.

1:28:04.572 --> 1:28:06.187
Please excuse me.

1:28:17.918 --> 1:28:19.294
I'm going for a walk.

1:29:43.045 --> 1:29:45.878
Kate. What's this?

1:29:48.551 --> 1:29:52.464
I'm going over with my father.
Anton has the other car.

1:29:52.638 --> 1:29:54.219
He'll take you when you're ready to go.

1:29:54.390 --> 1:29:58.053
- No, I'm talking about the bags.
- I was gonna catch the 6:30 flight.

1:29:58.269 --> 1:30:00.885
Tonight? After we skate?

1:30:01.146 --> 1:30:04.764
The house is paid up for two weeks, so
feel free to stay as long as you like.

1:30:04.984 --> 1:30:07.521
Kate, wait. What are you saying?
If this is about yesterday...

1:30:07.695 --> 1:30:08.935
I'm retiring.

1:30:11.907 --> 1:30:12.942
What?

1:30:16.495 --> 1:30:19.032
This afternoon is my final skate.

1:30:20.457 --> 1:30:22.448
- Kate, come on...
- You'll be fine.

1:30:24.461 --> 1:30:26.918
You won't have any trouble
finding another partner.

1:30:30.467 --> 1:30:34.380
Of course, they won't have
my wonderful slap shot.

1:30:37.057 --> 1:30:38.558
I gotta go get ready.

1:31:30.486 --> 1:31:33.193
Beautiful extension.
l/ery classy.

1:31:33.364 --> 1:31:34.820
Executed very nicely.

1:31:34.990 --> 1:31:37.026
I hope they can keep it
going to the ﬁnish.

1:31:50.422 --> 1:31:53.835
Neuman and Pekuro vsky
looking well-pos/tioned for a medal.

1:31:54.051 --> 1:31:57.384
Still to skate are Smilkov-Brushkin
and Kate Moseley and Doug Dorsey.

1:32:10.651 --> 1:32:12.733
Do you know what I think
would be wonderful?

1:32:14.279 --> 1:32:18.022
If you would go out there today
and skate for these people...

1:32:19.368 --> 1:32:21.074
...the way I have seen you skate.

1:32:25.457 --> 1:32:27.243
Enjoy each other.

1:32:52.860 --> 1:32:54.771
What's the matter?

1:32:55.612 --> 1:32:57.739
- Nothing.
- Are you all right?

1:33:10.878 --> 1:33:14.370
Kate, I'm sorry. My timing,
I know it stinks, but...

1:33:15.799 --> 1:33:19.212
I just keep thinking this thing
with us... it's gonna go away.

1:33:19.386 --> 1:33:22.844
I keep thinking if I can just
keep moving and checking,

1:33:23.015 --> 1:33:24.880
I'll get clear, but...

1:33:25.726 --> 1:33:27.591
Do you understand what I'm telling you?

1:33:27.770 --> 1:33:31.479
- I don't wanna fight anymore.
- No. I mean, yeah, I don't wanna fight.

1:33:31.648 --> 1:33:33.639
- Look, we have to skate.
- This won't wait.

1:33:33.859 --> 1:33:36.145
Kate, maybe I wasn't ready. Maybe...

1:33:36.320 --> 1:33:38.902
Maybe you didn't give me much
of a chance. Maybe...

1:33:39.073 --> 1:33:41.860
I don't know. Ijust... Ijust...

1:33:42.034 --> 1:33:43.774
Nine-six. Nine-three.

1:33:46.914 --> 1:33:49.200
Kate, somewhere in the middle
of all this, I fell in love with you.

1:33:50.542 --> 1:33:53.830
You may take the ice.

1:33:55.255 --> 1:33:58.839
I'm saying I love you.
I'm saying it out loud.

1:34:11.647 --> 1:34:15.310
Don't say we're not right for each
other. We may not be right for anybody.

1:34:15.984 --> 1:34:18.441
- You have to go on.
- Will you shut up a minute!

1:34:19.863 --> 1:34:22.980
It can't be any harder to stay together
than it was to stay apart.

1:34:23.158 --> 1:34:25.114
- Thirty seconds.
- Will you wait a minute?!

1:34:27.287 --> 1:34:30.245
Kate... I need you.

1:34:33.919 --> 1:34:35.034
I need you.

1:34:47.558 --> 1:34:49.173
We're doing the Pamchenko.

1:34:49.351 --> 1:34:52.309
- What?
- Oh, you heard me.

1:34:52.479 --> 1:34:54.720
Think I'm doing this
to get a program out of you?

1:34:54.940 --> 1:34:56.396
You wanna win, don't you?

1:34:57.359 --> 1:35:00.192
No. It's no good, Kate.
It's too dangerous.

1:35:00.362 --> 1:35:02.694
Then we agreed. We're putting it in.

1:35:07.452 --> 1:35:09.033
- It's out.
- It's in.

1:35:09.037 --> 1:35:10.117
- Out.
- In.

1:35:10.289 --> 1:35:11.369
- Out.
- In.

1:35:14.042 --> 1:35:16.499
- What difference does it make?
- The difference is...

1:35:16.670 --> 1:35:18.376
...I'm in the mood
to kick a little ass.

1:37:04.319 --> 1:37:07.186
- You didn't have to.
- Yes, I did.

1:37:08.156 --> 1:37:09.692
Why?

1:37:11.576 --> 1:37:12.952
Because I love you.

1:37:15.914 --> 1:37:17.654
Just remember who said it first.
